Aisha , wife to President Muhammadu Buhari has given update on the health status of her daughter, who recently returned from UK. DAILY POST had reported that her daughter went into self-isolation for 14 days upon her return from UK , one of the high risk countries of coronavirus. However, Aisha giving update on Thursday night, expressed delight that her daughter was doing fine and out of isolation. In a picture shared on her Twitter page, Aisah was seen hugging her daughter. Her tweet read: “It is a thing of joy and gratitude to Almighty God to reunite with my daughter after she had been in isolation for 14 days immediately she landed in Nigeria. “While I’m wishing all those infected for a speedy recovery, I pray for the end of this pandemic.” Meanwhile, 184 cases have been recorded cases in Nigeria.